metadata.name: Grande Dame #3
metadata.description:
Project inspired by the artworks of Vera Molnár ('Grande Dame' of digital art), one of the first women artists to use computers in her practice.

In January month of every year Π will party for Vera birth anniversary, artwork will come alive for the whole month.

Keys to interact:
[c] to change color mode (6 available)
[w] to raise wear level
[1] to [9] to change resolution
[s] to save as png (current settings)
[r] to reset all changes

Also in January:
[p] to pause/play animation
[r] to view standard artwork (paused)

Generative artwork by Gandhiavelli, @gandhiavelli. Made with p5js in 2022.

metadata.name: Magic Mushrooms #14
metadata.description:
Magic Mushrooms is an algorithm that generates 1990’s style random dot autostereogram drawings of psychedelic fungus.  I am not going to attempt to tell you how to see the mushrooms in these drawings.  Instead, you should watch a youtube video about stereograms or get very high with someone who was around in the 90s.

All due props and attribution go to the authors of the open source library stereogram.js, a modified version of which was used in this project to draw a bunch of colored squares in a grid that can trick the brains of some human beings into seeing magic mushrooms.  Like stereogram.js, this project is in no way affiliated with Magic Eye Inc.

Created by @capnganj - one love <3

metadata.name: Shine On You Crazy Diamond #14
metadata.description:
This artwork is an attempt to depict lights seen through textured and coloured glass windows. It's coded entirely in p5.js and is made of only rectangles, thousands of them.

Best viewed on a screen bigger than a mobile phone, while listening to this track called ‘Shine On You Crazy Diamond Parts I-V' by Pink Floyd: https://open.spotify.com/track/6pnwfWyaWjQiHCKTiZLItr

Artwork loads at 1000px by 1000px resolution by default. Press ‘2’,’4’ or ‘8’ to load as 2000px by 2000px, 4000px by 4000px or 8000px by 8000px respectively.
Press 's' at any time to download the rendered resolution.

Credits:
- Landed on this technique when experimenting with ideas in this essay by Tyler Hobbs: https://tylerxhobbs.com/essays/2015/creating-soft-textures-generatively
- Although my logic to create grids is slightly different, this blog by Gorilla Sun was a good starting point & guide: https://gorillasun.de/blog/an-algorithm-for-irregular-grids
- The name of the artwork is a tribute to my favourite band

metadata.name: Mugen #226
metadata.description:

Features:
- Style: 夢幻(fantasy)/無限(infinite)
- Density: Low/High
- Palette

- Press "s" key after the image is fully drawn: Saves 4200 x 3300 PNG

It may take some time for the drawing to complete, as it is drawn by lots of dots.
Made with p5js.
